top source apDictionary::init

result = apDictionary::init(_EXTRA=_EXTRA)

Initializes an apDictionary object.

Return value

Boolean success value (1/0)

Keywords

_EXTRA required

Keywords of the format FIELDNAME=VALUE. These define the initial class structure.

Examples

IDL> mydict = obj_new('apDictionary', strkey='hi', intkey=-3, objkey=obj_new())

top source apDictionary::add

apDictionary::add, _extra=_extra [, /SUCCESS]

Adds (multiple) field names and values.

Keywords

_extra required

Keywords of the format FIELDNAME=VALUE. The field names and values to add to the structure. If some of the fieldnames are already defined in the structure, they are overwritten.

SUCCESS optional type=boolean

Optional variable to store the success boolean flag.

top source apDictionary::set

apDictionary::set, _extra=_extra [, /SUCCESS]

Sets (multiple) field values.

Keywords

_extra required

Keywords of the format FIELDNAME=VALUE. The field names have to correspond to those of the class structure (not case-sensitive).

SUCCESS optional type=boolean

Optional variable to store the success boolean flag.

top source apDictionary::get

result = apDictionary::get(_extra=_extra [, /SUCCESS])

Retrieves a field value.

Return value

The value of the field.

Keywords

_extra required

Keyword of the format /FIELDNAME. The field name has to correspond to the name of a field in the class structure (not case-sensitive).

SUCCESS optional type=boolean

Optional variable to store the success boolean flag.
